PATTERNS WE REDESIGNED AS OUR OWN (inspired by, NOT vendored)
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

These BUCKS subsystems were STUDIED from the best prior art and RE-IMPLEMENTED
natively for BUCKS. We do not vendor or copy their code, and we do not brand BUCKS
internals after a source. We tip the hat here:

  - The deterministic event kernel / message bus (one engine, two clocks for
    backtest and live) — inspired by the NautilusTrader architecture and the
    crash-only / reconcile-on-boot pattern. Re-implemented as BUCKS's own kernel.

  - The order durability spine (deterministic client-order-ID, write-ahead intent
    journal, reconcile-from-broker on boot, explicit order state machine with
    cumulative-fill accounting) — informed by FIX-protocol ClOrdID idempotency and
    WAL/ARIES durability. BUCKS's own implementation.

  - The capability-probe pipeline (fetch a broker's OpenAPI/docs, draft a capability
    map, verify with read-only live calls, keep writes locked until a paper run +
    operator confirm) — BUCKS's own design over libopenapi.

  - The memory knowledge-graph / store — BUCKS's own lean SQLite + Obsidian-vault
    design, not a copy of any external KG.

  - The licensing gate and secrets-at-rest layer in this very package — BUCKS's own
    native implementations of widely-known ideas (license scanning; OS keychain with
    an age-encrypted fallback), not vendored tools.

All third-party CODE we link is credited above. The PATTERNS above are ours.
